news_raw.title: Nvidia-Backed Nebius Skyrockets On AI Cloud Computing Deal With Microsoft
news_raw.summary: Nebius stock skyrocketed after the Nvidia-backed AI cloud-computing firm struck a multiyear deal with Microsoft worth up to $19.4 billion.

news_raw.title: Morning Bid: Dollar slides as job worries mount
news_raw.summary: Global stocks pushed higher on Tuesday as U.S. rate cut fever built and a wave of European merger activity helped offset the week's political upheavals in France and Japan.  With U.S. long-term bond yields sliding to four-month lows on Monday ahead of the week's big debt auctions, the dollar fell to a seven-week low as expectations of big downward revisions to U.S. jobs data through last March reinforced bets on deeper Federal Reserve rate cuts.

news_raw.title: Morgan Stanley Says These 3 Stocks Are Top Picks for the Rest of 2025
news_raw.summary: We’re heading toward the final weeks of 3Q25, and while some investors have been cautious, the backdrop is far from bleak. Despite softer jobs data and September’s reputation as a difficult month for stocks, the major indexes remain near record highs. The S&P 500 has climbed 10% year-to-date, while the NASDAQ is up 12.5%. What’s fueling much of this resilience is growing confidence that the Federal Reserve will pivot back to rate cuts this month. news_raw.title: Nasdaq Builds on Record High Ahead of Key Jobs Data Revision
news_raw.summary: Stock futures were rising early Tuesday as investors awaited key jobs and inflation data, and a hotly anticipated Apple product launch event.  Futures on the Dow Jones Industrial Average were broadly flat early in the day, S&P 500 futures rose 0.1% and Nasdaq futures pointed 0.2% higher as tech stocks looked set to lead the market higher again after the index closed at a record high Monday.  Apple’s annual product event starts Tuesday, which could be another catalyst for the tech sector.

news_raw.title: Gold price hits another record high as US rate cut expectations rise
news_raw.summary: Bullion extends blistering rally as investors price in a near-certain rate cut by the US Federal Reserve.

news_raw.title: Why a Fed rate cut might not help the stock market
news_raw.summary: Markets are nearly certain the Fed will cut interest rates after weak jobs data, but some strategists warn that looser monetary policy could bring new risks for stocks.

news_raw.title: Is Block Stock Outperforming the Dow?
news_raw.summary: Block has significantly outperformed the Dow over the past year and in recent months, and analysts remain bullish on the stock’s longer-term prospects.

news_raw.title: Is Keurig Dr Pepper Stock Underperforming the Nasdaq?
news_raw.summary: Keurig Dr Pepper has significantly underperformed the Nasdaq Composite over the past year, yet analysts remain optimistic about the stock’s prospects.

news_raw.title: Heard on the Street Monday Recap: Down Payment
news_raw.summary: The average rate for a 30-year fixed mortgage fell to 6.29% Friday, the lowest level in 11 months and down 0.16 percentage point from Thursday, according to Mortgage News Daily.  Workers’ confidence in finding a new job if they lose their current one hit a record low, according to a survey by the New York Federal Reserve.  The poll also found Americans' inflation expectations were broadly stable.
